<subSubSection id="99F2651FFFB6FFECFF1CFDB44B81FB8B" pageId="7" pageNumber="100" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="D1573694FFB6FFECFF1CFDB44B4EFD2B" blockId="7.[113,764,610,1146]" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB6FFECFF1CFDB44992FD88" box="[151,240,610,633]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">Notes. –</emphasis>
Asingle specimen of original material, collected by 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB6FFECFF53FD544874FD68" box="[216,278,642,665]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">Pryon</emphasis>
in 
<collectingRegion id="132CF876FFB6FFECFEB1FD544805FD68" box="[314,359,642,665]" country="Indonesia" name="Jawa Timur" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">Java</collectingRegion>
, is present in G-PREL [G00800126] (
<figureCitation id="49D32A11FFB6FFECFFF1FD7449D8FD48" box="[122,186,673,698]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[136,164,1940,1959]" captionTargetBox="[306,1304,276,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-18@10.[306,1304,276,1863]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 5. – Lectotype of Polypodium glabrum Burm. f. in G-PREL." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5708791" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5708791/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Afurther Javanese specimen mentioned by Burman as (unnamed) variety could not be traced.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D1573694FFB6FFECFF1CFD344BACFCEB" blockId="7.[113,764,610,1146]" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">
The 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB6FFECFF4CFD344867FD08" box="[199,261,738,761]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">Pryon</emphasis>
specimen was cited by 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB6FFECFD89FD344BBDFD0B" author="MERRILL" box="[514,735,738,762]" firstAuthor="MERRILL" journalOrPublisher="Philippine J. Sci." page="337" pageId="7" pageNumber="100" pagination="329 - 388" part="19" refId="ref9969" refString="MERRILL, E. D. (1921). A review of the new species of plants proposed by N. L. Burman in his Flora Indica. Philippine J. Sci. 19: 329 - 388." title="A review of the new species of plants proposed by N. L. Burman in his Flora Indica" type="journal article" year="1921">MERRILL (1921: 337)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<typeStatus id="0E538836FFB6FFECFFFAFCD449C2FCEB" box="[113,160,770,794]" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">type</typeStatus>
. This is regarded as a valid implicit lectotypification.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D1573694FFB6FFECFF1CFCF44B81FB8B" blockId="7.[113,764,610,1146]" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">
The 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB6FFECFF4EFCF44860FCC8" box="[197,258,802,825]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">Pryon</emphasis>
specimen in G-PREL (
<figureCitation id="49D32A11FFB6FFECFE75FCF44B59FCC8" box="[510,571,801,826]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[136,164,1940,1959]" captionTargetBox="[306,1304,276,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-18@10.[306,1304,276,1863]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 5. – Lectotype of Polypodium glabrum Burm. f. in G-PREL." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5708791" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5708791/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
) clearly represents a species of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="16E84D17FFB6FFECFEE3FC944B56FCAB" authority="Schott" authorityName="Schott" box="[360,564,834,858]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Nephrolepidaceae" genus="Nephrolepis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="100" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB6FFECFEE3FC944883FCAB" box="[360,481,834,858]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">Nephrolepis</emphasis>
Schott
</taxonomicName>
. It corresponds to 
<taxonomicName id="16E84D17FFB6FFECFFFAFCB448B9FC8B" authority="(Sw.) Schott" authorityName="Schott" baseAuthorityName="Sw." box="[113,475,866,890]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Nephrolepidaceae" genus="Nephrolepis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="100" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="biserrata">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB6FFECFFFAFCB44828FC8B" box="[113,330,866,890]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">Nephrolepis biserrata</emphasis>
(Sw.) Schott
</taxonomicName>
, showing glabrous lamina, pinnate fronds, entire margin, pinnae articulate to rachis, hydathodes at vein endings. 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB6FFECFE3CFC744B0BFC48" author="BURMAN" box="[439,617,929,954]" firstAuthor="BURMAN" journalOrPublisher="Amsterdam" pageId="7" pageNumber="100" refId="ref8940" refString="BURMAN, N. L. (1768). Flora Indica: cui accedit series zoophytorum indicorum, nec non prodromus florae capensis. Amsterdam." title="Flora Indica: cui accedit series zoophytorum indicorum, nec non prodromus florae capensis" type="book" year="1768">BURMAN (1768)</bibRefCitation>
’s 
<taxonomicName id="16E84D17FFB6FFECFDF4FC7449A4FC2B" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Polypodiaceae" genus="Polypodium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="100" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glabrum">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB6FFECFDF4FC7449A4FC2B" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">Polypodium glabrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
predates 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB6FFECFEA0FC1448A9FC2B" author="SWARTZ" box="[299,459,962,986]" firstAuthor="SWARTZ" journalOrPublisher="J. Bot. (Schrader)" pageId="7" pageNumber="100" pagination="3 - 120" part="1800" refId="ref10356" refString="SWARTZ, O. (1801). Genera et species filicum. J. Bot. (Schrader) 1800 (2): 3 - 120." title="Genera et species filicum" type="journal article" year="1801">SWARTZ (1801)</bibRefCitation>
’s 
<taxonomicName id="16E84D17FFB6FFECFE55FC144BBCFC2B" authority="Sw. " authorityName="Sw. " box="[478,734,962,986]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Polypodiaceae" genus="Aspidium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="100" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="biserratum">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB6FFECFE55FC144BD1FC2B" box="[478,691,962,986]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">Aspidium biserratum</emphasis>
Sw.
</taxonomicName>
In order to allow the further use of a well-known and widely used fern name (A. Smith, pers. comm.) and to avoid disadvantageous nomenclatural changes entailed by the strict application of the ICN rules (
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB6FFECFEB8FB944B75FBAB" author="TURLAND" box="[307,535,1090,1114]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="TURLAND" pageId="7" pageNumber="100" refId="ref10318" refString="TURLAND, N. J., J. H. WIERSEMA, F. R. BARRIE, W. GREUTER, D. L. HAWKSWORTH, P. S. HERENDEEN, S. KNAPP, W. - H. KUSBER, D. - Z. LI, K. MARHOLD, T. W. MAY, J. MCNEILL, A. M. MONRO, J. PRADO, M. J. PRICE &amp; G. F. SMITH (2018). International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Veg. 159." title="International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017" type="proceedings" year="2018">TURLAND et al., 2018</bibRefCitation>
: Art. 14.1), a proposal to conserve Swartz’s name over Burman’s is in preparation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
